{"id":8539,"date":"2025-09-22T10:37:51","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T10:37:51","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8539"},"modified":"2025-12-04T11:44:47","modified_gmt":"2025-12-04T11:44:47","slug":"rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari\/","title":{"rendered":"RAMESHWAAM MADURAI KANYAKUMARI"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8839,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[101],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8539","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-exotic-tamilnadu","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8540],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8539","price":24777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":6,"nights":5,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Embark on a soul-stirring journey through Tamil Nadu\u2019s most sacred and historic destinations. Begin at <strong>Rameshwaram<\/strong>, one of the holiest pilgrimage sites in India, where the majestic Ramanathaswamy Temple with its world-famous corridors and the serene shores of Dhanushkodi create a divine atmosphere. Continue to <strong>Madurai<\/strong>, the cultural capital of Tamil Nadu, renowned for the magnificent Meenakshi Amman Temple, bustling bazaars, and centuries-old traditions of art, music, and dance. Conclude your journey at <strong>Kanyakumari<\/strong>, the southernmost tip of India, where the Arabian Sea, Bay of Bengal, and Indian Ocean meet. Witness the breathtaking sunrise and sunset, visit the <strong>Vivekananda Rock Memorial<\/strong>, and soak in the spiritual and natural beauty of this coastal town. This tour offers a perfect blend of <strong>pilgrimage, heritage, and scenic wonders<\/strong>, making it an unforgettable Tamil Nadu experience.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":" 3 star premium hotel stay\n All transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle\n Breakfast, Dinner, Lunch\n Toll Tax\n Parking\n Driver Allowance\nTravel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":" Any meals other than those mentioned above in inclusions\n Airfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\n All monument entry Fees\n Any portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature\n Any services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sightseeing points\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances, etc.\nAnything not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. What is the ideal duration for this trip? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A 5 to 6-day itinerary is recommended to comfortably cover Rameshwaram, Madurai, and Kanyakumari.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. Why is Rameshwaram considered sacred? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rameshwaram is one of the Char Dham pilgrimage sites, famous for Ramanathaswamy Temple, its long temple corridors, and sacred water tanks.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. What are the must-visit attractions in Madurai? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Meenakshi Amman Temple, Thirumalai Nayakkar Mahal, Gandhi Memorial Museum, and the bustling local markets.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. What is special about Kanyakumari? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is the southernmost tip of India, where the Arabian Sea, Bay of Bengal, and Indian Ocean meet. The Vivekananda Rock Memorial, Thiruvalluvar Statue, and sunrise\/sunset views are highlights.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"5. How do we travel between Rameshwaram, Madurai, and Kanyakumari? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By private car\/cab or coach. Train connectivity is also available, especially between Madurai and Rameshwaram\/Kanyakumari.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":374,"height":226,"file":"2025\/09\/rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1.png","filesize":160101,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-300x181.png","width":300,"height":181,"filesize":64441,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-300x181.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":31803,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-150x150.png"},"blog-sidebar-size":{"file":"rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-100x100.png","width":100,"height":100,"filesize":16431,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-100x100.png"},"blog-sidebar-size-thumb":{"file":"rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-90x80.png","width":90,"height":80,"filesize":12729,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/rameshwaam-madurai-kanyakumari-1-90x80.png"},"blog-post-two":{"file"